## OUTPUT STRUCTURE

# UNM Restructuring Report: {{.SystemName}}

## 1. Executive Summary
4-5 sentences: (a) overloaded teams + worst dimensions, (b) fragmented caps count, (c) at-risk/cross-team needs, (d) critical bottleneck, (e) highest-impact change. Use EXACT values from data.

## 2. Identified Value Streams
For each natural value stream from chains: name, actor needs served (exact names), current teams + span, recommended team (existing or [NEW]), services, capabilities, evidence.

## 3. Service Redistribution Plan
Table: | Service | Current Owner | Recommended Owner | Evidence |
Only include justified moves. Verify consistency with sections 4-6.

## 4. Capability Ownership Consolidation
For each fragmented capability: current split, consolidation target, services to move, trade-offs.

## 5. Overloaded Team Load Reduction
One subsection per high-load team: current dimensions (values+levels), services to move off (with targets+reasons), capabilities to reassign, projected load after ALL report changes, what remains.

## 6. Unlinked Capabilities & Modeling Gaps
For each unlinked capability: recommend identifying missing need, reclassifying visibility, or sunsetting.

## 7. Bottleneck & Coupling Mitigation
For critical bottlenecks: fan-in count, risk, architectural mitigation. For cross-team data coupling: ownership/decoupling strategy. Address critical path if depth≥4.

## 8. Team Structure Assessment
For EVERY team gaining/losing services: current state, recommended changes, net service count, expected dimension impact.

## 9. Interaction Mode Assessment
For overloaded/over-reliant team interactions: current→recommended mode with reasoning. Address isolated and over-reliant teams.

## 10. Prioritized Actions
Top 5-7 by structural impact. Each: exact entities, structural change, what improves, trade-off, dimension value changes.

## 11. Remaining Risks
What structural risks remain after changes: unresolved load, bottleneck, coupling, external dep concentration, critical path depth.
